sentences: Anne-Marie Rose Nicholson (born 7 April 1991), known mononymously as Anne-Marie, is an English singer.

She has attained charting singles on the UK Singles Chart, including Clean Bandit's "Rockabye", featuring Sean Paul, which peaked at number one, as well as "Alarm", "Ciao Adios", "Friends", "2002" and "Don't Play".
Her debut studio album, Speak Your Mind, was released on 27 April 2018, and peaked at number three on the UK Albums Chart.
She was nominated for four awards at the 2019 Brit Awards, including Best British Female Solo Artist.
In 2015, she signed a record deal with Asylum (a sub-label of Atlantic Records) and began releasing her work through the label.
Since 2021, she has been a coach on British singing competition The Voice UK.

She won Double Gold in the 2002 Funakoshi Shotokan Karate Association World Championships, Gold and Silver in the 2007 Funakoshi Shotokan Karate Association World Championships, and Gold in the United Kingdom Traditional Karate Federation National Championships.

She won Double Gold in the 2002 Funakoshi Shotokan Karate Association World Championships, Gold and Silver in the 2007 Funakoshi Shotokan Karate Association World Championships, and Gold in the United Kingdom Traditional Karate Federation National Championships.
She credits this with teaching her "discipline and focus – basically everything I need for this career" but now does not have time to practise it frequently, due to her performing commitments.
Anne-Marie has admitted that at school she was a nightmare, and that she feels bad for the teachers because she made their lives hell.
Anne-Marie cut a solo demo for Rocket Records in 2013 called "Summer Girl".

She spent two years touring alongside them.

On 10 June 2015, Anne-Marie released her debut EP Karate, which went out on the new label Major Tom's; two singles were released from it, "Karate" and "Gemini", which led to Anne-Marie making her first solo live performances.
That November she released "Do It Right", which peaked at number 90 on the UK Singles Chart.
On 20 May 2016, Anne-Marie released "Alarm", the first single from her debut album.
It spent one week at number 76 in June before resurfacing a month later; it later peaked at number 2 and was certified Platinum in the UK.

The song was released on 9 February 2018, and was Anne-Marie's second top five UK hit as a lead artist.
On 22 February, Anne-Marie announced that her debut studio album, Speak Your Mind, would be released on 27 April 2018.

In November 2018, Anne-Marie and James Arthur recorded "Rewrite the Stars" from The Greatest Showman for the re-recording of its soundtrack, The Greatest Showman: Reimagined.
